    <introduction xml:id="auto_mrddhsce">
        <p xml:id="auto_pqi4zymy">
            By the end of this topic, you should be able to:
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_7deyh9hc">
            <ol xml:id="auto_7k1v7qwf">
                <li xml:id="auto_0phdjwr1">
                    <p xml:id="auto_8h7m0anf">
                       Define and apply trigonometric ratios (sine, cosine, tangent).
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_xg93n0fq">
                    <p xml:id="auto_ohye8o7t">
                       
                        Solve for unknown sides and angles using trigonometric ratios.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_wn7o4lvu">
                    <p xml:id="auto_y71r6k97">
                        Apply trigonometric values of special 
                        angles (<m>30^\circ, \,45^\circ, \,60^\circ</m>) in solving geometric problems.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_jj4aq5u0">
                    <p xml:id="auto_7n6r7p8a">
                        Analyze and interpret relationships between angles and side lengths 
                        in various contexts to solve application problems.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
       

